history.content:
Are you looking for an opportunity to learn technical, social, and project-management skills in a fun environment? Do you want to be a part of a diverse and intelligent community that uses technology to address societal problems?

If so, Tech+ Social Impact is the organization for you! We are a student-run club at U.C. Berkeley that focuses on building and executing technological projects for social good, specifically in the fields of healthcare, education, and women in tech. We are also part of the national TechShift Alliance. More information can be found at our Facebook Page: www.facebook.com/TechImpactBerkeley

We welcome all majors, backgrounds, and skill levels to become a part of our family! The Tech+ Social Impact club on campus is now accepting applications for Fall 2019. Here’s our application: https://forms.gle/BPbPinexdqPGZr4S7. The application is due on September 10th at 11:59pm.

print(“Ready! Set! Reform!”)
